Package ca.mcgill.splendorserver.model.action

Class Move

java.lang.Object
ca.mcgill.splendorserver.model.action.Move
public class Move extends Object
Represents a move with the action a player made, the card that was purchased/reserved (if any) and the username of the player.

  • Constructor Details

    • Move

      public Move(Action action, Card card, PlayerWrapper player, DeckType deckType, TokenType returnedTokenTypes, Noble noble, TradingPostSlot tradingPostSlot, TokenType selectedTokenTypes)
      Creates a Move.
      Parameters:
      action - The action that a player did.
      card - The card that was purchased/reserved, can be null if none or not available to see by the client.
      player - The player's username.
      deckType - The level of the deck from which they can take from if they want, can be null.
      returnedTokenTypes - tokens that are to be returned as a result of having > 10 tokens as a result of the tokens taken in this move.
      noble - a noble tile that represents the noble which will visit as a result of selecting this move
      tradingPostSlot - The trading post slot that the player is acquiring a power from
      selectedTokenTypes - The type(s) of token if any, can be null.
